===Etymology===
From Proto-Sino-Tibetan; cognate with {{cog|bo|བླ}} and {{cog|my|လိပ်ပြာ|လိပ်'''ပြာ'''}}.

Related to {{och-l|白|white}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

; "illuminated part of the moon"
: {{zh-ref|Wang (1923)}} in {{lang|zh|《生霸死霸考》}} supports the definition by examining textual traditions of the Chinese classics and archaeological evidences from the {{w|Western Zhou}} era ({{circa2|11th–8th centuries {{BCE}}|short=yes}}). {{w|Chinese bronze inscriptions|Bronze script}} texts from the era commonly use the form {{och-l|霸}}.

; "dark part of the moon"
: Chiefly found in some old dictionaries based on another textual tradition, traced by {{zh-ref|Wang (1923)}} to the calendrical innovations of {{w|Liu Xin (scholar)|Liu Xin}} and later Confucian "[[pseudepigraphy]]".

